txt.en: Spiders and their captured prey can be found in Shak Phêlex, on the eastern side of Tâkhdar.\n\nSlay spiders throughout Tilmakhím and collect Ilzhâna's missing probably-not-contraband parcels. The spiders probably dragged them back to their nest in Shak Phêlex.
Ilzhâna can be found at Tilmakhím on the western side of Tâkhdar.\n\nReturn to Ilzhâna with the parcels.
'I cannot continue my reputable business and share my incredible deals until those parcels are returned to me and the spiders dealt with, my dear friend and future customer!'
Collect the trader's misplaced shipment parcels ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'You return victorious, my capable and discreet new friend! And you did not... steal a peek inside those unassuming crates, no? Excellent, excellent! I knew you were to be trusted.\n\n'Your reward, for business well conducted!'
Collect the trader's misplaced shipment parcels ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Ilzhâna, a perfectly legitimate trader in Tilmakhím, has asked you to recover some missing parcels and slay the spiders who stole them. She asked you not to look inside.

'You have a good eye for honest business, friend! I assure you, every single one of my legitimate wares has legitimate paperwork from legitimate origins!

'It pains me to say, but you have come to trade at a bad time. I fear some scoundrel has made off with my latest shipment. That spider nest to the north-east causes much trouble for honest traders like myself.

'Recover my shipment and you shall be amply rewarded, friend! Doubly so for your subtlety!'
